documented_sage_files.non_semistable_primes.non_semistable_primes(f)¶

Return list of primes of non-semistable reduction

INPUT: - f – univariate polynomial over \ZZ; must be of degree 5

or 6.

OUTPUT:

A list of primes p at which the curve y^2 = f(x) has non-semistable reduction.

EXAMPLES: TODO

Note

The list returned is probably larger than the list that we really want most of the time; we are just taking the primes which divide the conductor with exponent at least 2.
